The paper focuses on improving the performance of deep learning tasks with insufficient training data, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a method for identifying and using a subset of training images, which involves feature extraction and selection, suggesting that it may also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on multiple visual classification tasks, indicating that it may be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
